    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen editing two or more windows in `vsplit`, when I scroll in the right window (CTRL-D/CTRL-E/...), then window on the left gets \"partially scrolled\", see the video:\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6361d08b-64fc-4552-a250-ba412cd30b9f\n\nThis might be similar to https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34512, but it's not only for floating windows.\n\nThis bug doesn't happen on latest stable.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean somefile\nvsplit\n<c-w>l\n<c-d>\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nScrolling one window doesn't mess up the others.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-914+gb79ff967ac\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim v9.1.1591\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR, but also checked using nightly AppImage from Github",
